# candidates.json is regenerated by CI from Wikidata + Wikipedia on every
# workflow run. To prevent divergent-bot-commit merge conflicts between
# main and feature branches, the build_candidates step in
# .github/workflows/pages.yml only commits the file when running on `main`.
# On feature branches it's only uploaded as a workflow artifact and never
# tracked in the branch.
#
# Defensive flags below keep things tidy if the file ever does drift:
#   - linguist-generated=true  collapses the file in GitHub PR diffs
#   - -merge                   skips 3-way merging; on the rare hand-edit
#                              conflict, the merge target's version wins
#                              (main is always the source of truth)
candidates.json linguist-generated=true -merge
